It has been one incredible journey, but I can’t believe the time is almost here. Any moment now, I’m going to be a mother and I can’t wait to share parenthood with @neil_diemond ❤️
📸: @andreahunterphotography 

I’ve always put my heart and soul into my work, putting every ounce of blood, sweat and tears into my passions. There were several points in my life where being a parent just wasn’t in the books. I was so laser focused on success and achievement that it never occurred to me to be possible.

Now, I’m more than ready to be the absolute best I can be, not only as a musician, but as a mother and a partner. I want to continue to spark inspiration in those who want to pursue music and know it is possible to achieve your dreams. I want to inspire other mothers and fathers to keep fighting the good fight. And most importantly, I want to inspire our baby to do the same each day.

I can’t wait to share this new chapter with you all. Thank you for all the continual love and support. Without you, I wouldn’t be where I am today. Keep the metal alive 🤘🏼🤘🏼❤️❤️

Welcome to the world, little Jet Merrick Autry ❤️ 

On Jan 26th, this little shredder arrived after 31 hours of labor (in my Iron Maiden t-shirt 🤘🏼). To be honest, I knew little about being a parent. I hadn’t even changed a diaper, and the only lullabies I know are headbangers. 

But one thing is for certain, I never knew I could love something so much and so fully until he was in my arms. 

I can’t wait for what’s to come in this new chapter. So here’s to new beginnings, new jammy jams, and new adventures. 🎸👶🏻❤️

✨ 5 years sober today ✨

Honestly, if you asked me 6 years ago if I’d imagine my life the way it is now, there’s absolutely no way. I truly believed I would drink until the day I died, living fast and dying young.

I’m not here to tell you that drinking and partying is bad. By all means, if you enjoy it and you have it under control, live it up!

But from my personal experience, I was slowly falling apart while keeping up an appearance of having my shit together. Outside were smiles, laughs, and hard work. Inside, I was falling apart at the seams, dousing my real problems with liquid courage. 

It wasn’t until I decided to start training Muay Thai and boxing that I finally found something that gave me more of a rush than a glass in my hand. I went full force, training 8-9 hours a week to the point where drinking just wasn’t an option anymore. 

I not only saw a physical change, but an emotional change.  Fighting gave me confidence I’d never known before, that even playing the stage couldn’t rival. I rediscovered loving myself and caring for my mind and body again.

Now, I have all the more reason to continue on my sober journey to be the absolute best example I can be for little Jet. So here’s to many more years of sobriety and to all those that gave me love and support during such a tough time. ❤️

If you struggle with addiction, know that there is a way out. You can pull through. It won’t be easy, hell it’ll probably be one of the most difficult things you so. But I promise it’s worth it in the end.

It’s my birthday! 🎂🎸

Here’s to another year of existence. It’s been one whirlwind of a journey the last few years. From living in a 400 sq ft studio apartment grinding out guitar videos every day for two years straight to building a whole new life and family with my love @neil_diemond and baby Jet, I can’t describe how grateful I am for every step of the journey, the good, the bad, and the ugly. 

Most importantly, I am grateful for each and every one of you supporting and watching my videos. For those who have been here from the beginning Nylon Pink days, fans and supports of She Demons and @vigilofwar , those who followed my travel and food adventures with @kailayu and those who stumbled upon my guitar videos in your feeds, thank you for taking the time to appreciate the music and metuhlll. 

So here’s to 34! And hopefully many more!

If you feel like celebrating with me, feel free to join my OF or shop my store in the link in my bio. ❤️

2023 Recap ❤️ Happy New Year! 🎆 

It’s been an absolute wild ride this 2023. Never in my life did I think I’d be where I am today, and I wouldn’t change it for the world. 

✅I gave birth to our beautiful son Jet Merrick Autry with the best partner and father one could ask for @neil_diemond . Maternity photo by @andreahunterphotography 
✅ Saw my @vigilofwar fam in Phoenix @aliciavigil @shanetaylorinsta @iamchristopherwilson .
✅ Learned how to mom when I had no idea how. 
✅ @bescene chopped my hair and made me a blonde bombshell
✅ Spent the most amazing time with my family I have in a while. 
✅ Drove from Phoenix -> LA -> Sactown 3 times this year with baby under 1 solo. Got to see da homie @tylerfromjupiter 
✅ @kailayu @ramborivera and I saw our lil sis @jamiescoles get married 
✅ Jet met Uncle @pat_bastid and now needs to meet Uncle @crocugly 
✅ Released a single with the legendary @otepofficial @esjayjones1 
✅ Released a single with RAMENSTEIN @miaasanomusic @tinaguo @gkellymusic 
✅ Got tattooed by @salvatattoo @strugglemadetattoo 
✅ Met Jet’s arch nemesis Santa Claus
✅ Participated in @j4r3dd1n3s biggest shred collab again
✅ Built a loving family of my own. 

So here’s to 2024! Ready for everything that’s to come.  Thank you all for the love and support. Without you, I wouldn’t be where I am today. 🤘🏼❤️
